    },
    {
      "id": "BgierBbm03JezO3zBLdy7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 892.8233114213419,
      "y": 43352.19044892791,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bS9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 66812457,
      "version": 151,
      "versionNonce": 484038441,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q Lets say we have two hardisks one is of 10 GB another one is of 10 GB and the file we want to store\n    is somewhere of 15 GB, how we will store?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q Lets say we have two hardisks one is of 10 GB another one is of 10 GB and the file we want to store\n    is somewhere of 15 GB, how we will store?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GOElfWXk_JCdCjhkM217p",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 968.4717489213419,
      "y": 43419.15529267791,
      "width": 1012,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bSC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1173874727,
      "version": 1619,
      "versionNonce": 397495271,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If we will mount whole 10 GB in one folder or directory then also we can store 10 GB file \nonly, we can't mount two disks at one location, also if we can then some part will be in\nfirst some will be in second\n\nSo what we will try to do is we will take both disks and we will try to somehow join these\n2 disks. And when we join them together we create a bigger storage space, out of that lets \nsay 15 GB is needed so we will carve a space or a partition of 15 GB and we will use that\npartition to be mounter over one directory so that we can use that space for 15 GB storage.\nactually this is why Google drive or any other drive out there provide us space.\nWhat they do they create this kind of structure where in whatever we need lets say we need\n1 TB or 5 TB or 15 TB of storage, they are not adding a single HDD. What they are doing is\nthat whenever lets say in their storage server , in cloud computing there is not just like\na single server of everything there are separate storage servers, there are RAM cluster, \nthere are CPU cluster everything. So in their storage server people are coming and keep on\ntaking storage.\nWhat happens if they run out of storage they will add more Hardisk and that will become a \npart of entire storage. And the more people come and the more they want to consume they will\nkeep on expanding like this.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If we will mount whole 10 GB in one folder or directory then also we can store 10 GB file \nonly, we can't mount two disks at one location, also if we can then some part will be in\nfirst some will be in second\n\nSo what we will try to do is we will take both disks and we will try to somehow join these\n2 disks. And when we join them together we create a bigger storage space, out of that lets \nsay 15 GB is needed so we will carve a space or a partition of 15 GB and we will use that\npartition to be mounter over one directory so that we can use that space for 15 GB storage.\nactually this is why Google drive or any other drive out there provide us space.\nWhat they do they create this kind of structure where in whatever we need lets say we need\n1 TB or 5 TB or 15 TB of storage, they are not adding a single HDD. What they are doing is\nthat whenever lets say in their storage server , in cloud computing there is not just like\na single server of everything there are separate storage servers, there are RAM cluster, \nthere are CPU cluster everything. So in their storage server people are coming and keep on\ntaking storage.\nWhat happens if they run out of storage they will add more Hardisk and that will become a \npart of entire storage. And the more people come and the more they want to consume they will\nkeep on expanding like this.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1PZRufUNsvT3dPJDVViup",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 969.0537801713419,
      "y": 43926.94826142791,
      "width": 1078,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bSD",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 449223,
      "version": 501,
      "versionNonce": 1875315209,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What we will do right now is, We will take 2 disks somehow combine them together, \nRight now we have a single disk sdb is attached to our system what we will try to do is rather\nthan doing it on two different disks we will try to do on two parition, We will create 2 partition\nlets say of 100 or 200 MB each, And after doing it on two partitions of 200 MB each, same way\nwe can do on multiple disks also.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What we will do right now is, We will take 2 disks somehow combine them together, \nRight now we have a single disk sdb is attached to our system what we will try to do is rather\nthan doing it on two different disks we will try to do on two parition, We will create 2 partition\nlets say of 100 or 200 MB each, And after doing it on two partitions of 200 MB each, same way\nwe can do on multiple disks also.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4SHhmm9bMKvBtA0oLw9Uv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1029.807686421342,
      "y": 44096.82716767791,
      "width": 484,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
