    {
      "id": "CgX5JumqMPXQ_cIwb_-ii",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1909.663155171342,
      "y": 53954.55763642791,
      "width": 187,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 775956165,
      "version": 90,
      "versionNonce": 397833609,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Rest of the world",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Rest of the world",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "aOBBLJtbF_5EY11w3IQ2x",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1077.491280171342,
      "y": 54152.27248017791,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1248076107,
      "version": 1000,
      "versionNonce": 1027359623,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There is a concept called as static IP wherein we can go to our system and configure IP and that will\nsync with the router and our router will not this is the specific IP that we will be using and\nthat becomes our static IP address.\n\n\nOnce Our system gets a IP address via DHCP server, SO DHCP server not only shares us IP, it also\nshares some additional details, we will check in sometime\n\nBut before that other things also we need to check\nIf there is a browser cache or OS level cache so we need to clear those caches\n\nthen we need to check if there is a static IP, if its a static IP and we might have configured a wrong\nIP, so we can again move to a dyanamic IP and then configure or check with router if the connection is\nable to go out or not. So we have to check for static IP.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There is a concept called as static IP wherein we can go to our system and configure IP and that will\nsync with the router and our router will not this is the specific IP that we will be using and\nthat becomes our static IP address.\n\n\nOnce Our system gets a IP address via DHCP server, SO DHCP server not only shares us IP, it also\nshares some additional details, we will check in sometime\n\nBut before that other things also we need to check\nIf there is a browser cache or OS level cache so we need to clear those caches\n\nthen we need to check if there is a static IP, if its a static IP and we might have configured a wrong\nIP, so we can again move to a dyanamic IP and then configure or check with router if the connection is\nable to go out or not. So we have to check for static IP.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0golXyKs7a2LrOzbZQTWW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1066.670967671342,
      "y": 54547.45998017791,
      "width": 704,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 669226219,
      "version": 48,
      "versionNonce": 1983962217,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Next we check for our Gateway, Is our Gateway Ip correct or not?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Next we check for our Gateway, Is our Gateway Ip correct or not?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "h1m3cFa9jqy5Tm14y6TLh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1122.932686421342,
      "y": 54596.49513642791,
      "width": 11,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 732363083,
      "version": 4,
      "versionNonce": 395738059,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772263267067,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "NBlp0zMrTTWvGXCdJFgLt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1139.323311421342,
      "y": 54593.45998017791,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 70100421,
      "version": 979,
      "versionNonce": 806894247,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Gateway itself is the point that is our connection to rest of the world, Like if we need to connect\nto the rest of the world, I am going out via my router, My router makes me connect to Rest of the\nworld So my router is my Gateway and router is also a device and to connect to a device we need\ndevice's IP address, So when we first time do the DHCP thing with our router, Router also gives\nus its own IP address to note. And maybe we are doing something and by mistake we went to the file\nand we changed that IP address, So our IP of our gateway is changed and now when our system is \ntrying to hit the gateway we are not able to. So we have to check our Gateway IP address\n\nQ -> DO reseach and find where we get the file where we have the Gateway IP also give the command\nwe can check via command\nip route default\nor \nip route show -> this will give default gateway IP",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Gateway itself is the point that is our connection to rest of the world, Like if we need to connect\nto the rest of the world, I am going out via my router, My router makes me connect to Rest of the\nworld So my router is my Gateway and router is also a device and to connect to a device we need\ndevice's IP address, So when we first time do the DHCP thing with our router, Router also gives\nus its own IP address to note. And maybe we are doing something and by mistake we went to the file\nand we changed that IP address, So our IP of our gateway is changed and now when our system is \ntrying to hit the gateway we are not able to. So we have to check our Gateway IP address\n\nQ -> DO reseach and find where we get the file where we have the Gateway IP also give the command\nwe can check via command\nip route default\nor \nip route show -> this will give default gateway IP",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "B9o0ABS1ogdmItopg1zCa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1064.635811421342,
      "y": 54979.10060517791,
      "width": 1078,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1457104235,
      "version": 168,
      "versionNonce": 681273161,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Next lets say our Gateway is also set, we are able to hit our router but still the things are not \nworking due to we are not able to hit that particular website",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Next lets say our Gateway is also set, we are able to hit our router but still the things are not \nworking due to we are not able to hit that particular website",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "amcpIW3EEE8pk_UYi4LN7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1126.819405171342,
      "y": 55062.74513642791,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bVP",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 603695621,
      "version": 1198,
      "versionNonce": 1319652807,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775105901859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In Linux or Systems there is a concept called as Firewall, and firewall generall block the\nrequest in two ways\none is called as whitelisting and another is called as blacklisting\nblacklist is the term that we hear very often like kisi bhi particular website to blacklist\nkr diya h, we can't access that website, \nBlacklisting basically means that we block the domain name so they block google.com, we will\nnot be able to hit google.com\n\nWhitelisting basically means that we are not only blacklisting the domain name, we are actually\ncutting off all the IP addresses also related to it. So if we block at the IP level then it\nis called as whitelisting, So neither we can reach out to domain name nor the IP addresses. Our\npacket would not go forward to that IP.\n\nSo we have to check our firewall rules also.\n\nIn linux there is command for firewall which is\n\nufw -> to check our firewall -> dont run in terminal it might happen we are not able to use\n        our system properly ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In Linux or Systems there is a concept called as Firewall, and firewall generall block the\nrequest in two ways\none is called as whitelisting and another is called as blacklisting\nblacklist is the term that we hear very often like kisi bhi particular website to blacklist\nkr diya h, we can't access that website, \nBlacklisting basically means that we block the domain name so they block google.com, we will\nnot be able to hit google.com\n\nWhitelisting basically means that we are not only blacklisting the domain name, we are actually\ncutting off all the IP addresses also related to it. So if we block at the IP level then it\nis called as whitelisting, So neither we can reach out to domain name nor the IP addresses. Our\npacket would not go forward to that IP.\n\nSo we have to check our firewall rules also.\n\nIn linux there is command for firewall which is\n\nufw -> to check our firewall -> dont run in terminal it might happen we are not able to use\n        our system properly ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
