      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Great — now let’s convert this **Elevator System into Django schema design (DB models)**.\n\nThink like this 👇\n👉 DB is mainly for **state persistence + tracking**, not real-time movement\n👉 Real-time logic (queues, movement) stays in memory / services\n\n---\n\n# 🗄️ Django Schema Design (Models)\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Elevator Model\n\n```python\nfrom django.db import models\n\nclass Elevator(models.Model):\n    DIRECTION_CHOICES = [\n        ('UP', 'UP'),\n        ('DOWN', 'DOWN'),\n        ('IDLE', 'IDLE')\n    ]\n\n    current_floor = models.IntegerField(default=0)\n    direction = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=DIRECTION_CHOICES, default='IDLE')\n    capacity = models.IntegerField()\n    current_load = models.IntegerField(default=0)\n    is_active = models.BooleanField(default=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Elevator {self.id} at floor {self.current_floor}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Floor Model\n\n```python\nclass Floor(models.Model):\n    floor_number = models.IntegerField(unique=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Floor {self.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Request Model (Important)\n\n👉 Handles both:\n\n* External request (floor button)\n* Internal request (inside elevator)\n\n```python\nclass Request(models.Model):\n    REQUEST_TYPE = [\n        ('EXTERNAL', 'External'),\n        ('INTERNAL', 'Internal')\n    ]\n\n    DIRECTION_CHOICES = [\n        ('UP', 'UP'),\n        ('DOWN', 'DOWN'),\n        (None, 'None')\n    ]\n\n    floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    direction = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=DIRECTION_CHOICES, null=True, blank=True)\n    request_type = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=REQUEST_TYPE)\n    \n    assigned_elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.SET_NULL, null=True, blank=True)\n\n    is_completed = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"{self.request_type} request at floor {self.floor.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4️⃣ Elevator Stop / Queue Model\n\n👉 This replaces in-memory queue when persistence is needed\n\n```python\nclass ElevatorStop(models.Model):\n    STATUS_CHOICES = [\n        ('PENDING', 'Pending'),\n        ('DONE', 'Done')\n    ]\n\n    elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='stops')\n    floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    sequence = models.IntegerField()  # order of execution\n    status = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=STATUS_CHOICES, default='PENDING')\n\n    class Meta:\n        ordering = ['sequence']\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Elevator {self.elevator.id} -> Floor {self.floor.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5️⃣ (Optional) Trip / Ride Model\n\n👉 Useful for analytics (real-world systems)\n\n```python\nclass Trip(models.Model):\n    elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    start_floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='trip_start')\n    end_floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='trip_end')\n    \n    start_time = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)\n    end_time = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Trip {self.id} - Elevator {self.elevator.id}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n# 🔄 How This Maps to Flow\n\n### Step Mapping 👇\n\n| Flow Step                   | DB Model                     |\n| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n| User presses button         | `Request (EXTERNAL)`         |\n| Controller assigns elevator | `assigned_elevator` updated  |\n| Elevator queue updated      | `ElevatorStop` created       |\n| Elevator reaches floor      | `ElevatorStop.status = DONE` |\n| User selects destination    | `Request (INTERNAL)`         |\n| Trip tracking               | `Trip`                       |\n\n---\n\n# ⚡ Important Design Decisions (Interview Gold)\n\n### ❗ Why not store queue only in DB?\n\n* DB is slow for real-time operations\n* Use:\n\n  * **In-memory queue (Redis / heap)**\n  * DB only for persistence\n\n---\n\n### ❗ Handling Concurrency\n\nUse:\n\n```python\nfrom django.db import transaction\n\nwith transaction.atomic():\n    elevator = Elevator.objects.select_for_update().get(id=elevator_id)\n    # safe update\n```\n\n---\n\n### ❗ Indexing (Very Important)\n\n```python\nclass Request(models.Model):\n    class Meta:\n        indexes = [\n            models.Index(fields=['is_completed']),\n            models.Index(fields=['assigned_elevator']),\n        ]\n```\n\n---\n\n# 🧠 Final Architecture Thought\n\n👉 Combine both:\n\n* **DB (Django models)** → state, history, analytics\n* **In-memory system** → fast decision making\n* **Controller Service** → brain of system\n\n---\n\n# 🚀 If You Want Next Step\n\nI can extend this to:\n\n✅ REST APIs (Django views/DRF)\n✅ Redis-based queue design\n✅ Thread-safe production architecture\n✅ How Google / Otis elevators actually optimize\n\nJust tell me 👍\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Great — now let’s convert this **Elevator System into Django schema design (DB models)**.\n\nThink like this 👇\n👉 DB is mainly for **state persistence + tracking**, not real-time movement\n👉 Real-time logic (queues, movement) stays in memory / services\n\n---\n\n# 🗄️ Django Schema Design (Models)\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Elevator Model\n\n```python\nfrom django.db import models\n\nclass Elevator(models.Model):\n    DIRECTION_CHOICES = [\n        ('UP', 'UP'),\n        ('DOWN', 'DOWN'),\n        ('IDLE', 'IDLE')\n    ]\n\n    current_floor = models.IntegerField(default=0)\n    direction = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=DIRECTION_CHOICES, default='IDLE')\n    capacity = models.IntegerField()\n    current_load = models.IntegerField(default=0)\n    is_active = models.BooleanField(default=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Elevator {self.id} at floor {self.current_floor}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Floor Model\n\n```python\nclass Floor(models.Model):\n    floor_number = models.IntegerField(unique=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Floor {self.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Request Model (Important)\n\n👉 Handles both:\n\n* External request (floor button)\n* Internal request (inside elevator)\n\n```python\nclass Request(models.Model):\n    REQUEST_TYPE = [\n        ('EXTERNAL', 'External'),\n        ('INTERNAL', 'Internal')\n    ]\n\n    DIRECTION_CHOICES = [\n        ('UP', 'UP'),\n        ('DOWN', 'DOWN'),\n        (None, 'None')\n    ]\n\n    floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    direction = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=DIRECTION_CHOICES, null=True, blank=True)\n    request_type = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=REQUEST_TYPE)\n    \n    assigned_elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.SET_NULL, null=True, blank=True)\n\n    is_completed = models.BooleanField(default=False)\n    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"{self.request_type} request at floor {self.floor.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4️⃣ Elevator Stop / Queue Model\n\n👉 This replaces in-memory queue when persistence is needed\n\n```python\nclass ElevatorStop(models.Model):\n    STATUS_CHOICES = [\n        ('PENDING', 'Pending'),\n        ('DONE', 'Done')\n    ]\n\n    elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='stops')\n    floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    sequence = models.IntegerField()  # order of execution\n    status = models.CharField(max_length=10, choices=STATUS_CHOICES, default='PENDING')\n\n    class Meta:\n        ordering = ['sequence']\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Elevator {self.elevator.id} -> Floor {self.floor.floor_number}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5️⃣ (Optional) Trip / Ride Model\n\n👉 Useful for analytics (real-world systems)\n\n```python\nclass Trip(models.Model):\n    elevator = models.ForeignKey(Elevator, on_delete=models.CASCADE)\n    start_floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='trip_start')\n    end_floor = models.ForeignKey(Floor, on_delete=models.CASCADE, related_name='trip_end')\n    \n    start_time = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)\n    end_time = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"Trip {self.id} - Elevator {self.elevator.id}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n# 🔄 How This Maps to Flow\n\n### Step Mapping 👇\n\n| Flow Step                   | DB Model                     |\n| --------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n| User presses button         | `Request (EXTERNAL)`         |\n| Controller assigns elevator | `assigned_elevator` updated  |\n| Elevator queue updated      | `ElevatorStop` created       |\n| Elevator reaches floor      | `ElevatorStop.status = DONE` |\n| User selects destination    | `Request (INTERNAL)`         |\n| Trip tracking               | `Trip`                       |\n\n---\n\n# ⚡ Important Design Decisions (Interview Gold)\n\n### ❗ Why not store queue only in DB?\n\n* DB is slow for real-time operations\n* Use:\n\n  * **In-memory queue (Redis / heap)**\n  * DB only for persistence\n\n---\n\n### ❗ Handling Concurrency\n\nUse:\n\n```python\nfrom django.db import transaction\n\nwith transaction.atomic():\n    elevator = Elevator.objects.select_for_update().get(id=elevator_id)\n    # safe update\n```\n\n---\n\n### ❗ Indexing (Very Important)\n\n```python\nclass Request(models.Model):\n    class Meta:\n        indexes = [\n            models.Index(fields=['is_completed']),\n            models.Index(fields=['assigned_elevator']),\n        ]\n```\n\n---\n\n# 🧠 Final Architecture Thought\n\n👉 Combine both:\n\n* **DB (Django models)** → state, history, analytics\n* **In-memory system** → fast decision making\n* **Controller Service** → brain of system\n\n---\n\n# 🚀 If You Want Next Step\n\nI can extend this to:\n\n✅ REST APIs (Django views/DRF)\n✅ Redis-based queue design\n✅ Thread-safe production architecture\n✅ How Google / Otis elevators actually optimize\n\nJust tell me 👍\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
